Titans are powerful and mighty beings that will unleash their rage on the board and act as unpredictable hazards. These mythical entities won&rsquo;t be swayed easily, but predicting their moves and controlling their rage could very well become your ticket to victory&hellip;

If your civilization has been paying attention to legends and has acquired enough Talismans, you will be equipped to handle the Titans and even use their power &ndash; neglect them and you might become the unlucky target of their rampage!

Like Monsters, Titans will appear on the board at the flip of one of the new Barbarian/Titan tokens.

As soon as they appear, they will immediately start wreaking havoc on Provinces&hellip;

While Typhon is in play, all players must pay a tribute at the end of their turn (or at the end of the round in continuous play) ; either pay 1 talisman token, 2 Gold, or sacrifice one Soldier (put it back in the box). You may abandon a Province as a result IF you have no other available soldiers to sacrifice.

Typhon gets removed from play at the end of the active player's turn (or end of active round in Continuous Play) where there are no Talisman tokens left on the map.

Mimes Intense et Tordus is is an out of the ordinary party game. In this game for adults, two teams compete in a merciless battle of wacky mimes. One player has to make his team guess concepts in the required time. But beware! There are several twists:

     At any time, your teammates can join you to help you mime;
     The hourglass does not indicate the end of the round: it indicates the moment when the opposing team starts throwing a foam ball at you! As long as you don't get hit by the ball, you can continue to accumulate points;
     The spiral tiles allow you to make your opponents' task more difficult or simplify yours (whether you have to mime or throw the ball);
     Two difficulty modes are included: the green cards contain more neutral subjects and the pink ones, more daring.


As the name suggests, this game is really intense, and definitely twisted.

